The `--exclude` flag currently takes exact paths, right? Since v2.1.4 stabilized the path matching internals, you have a clean foundation to build glob support on top of.
Here's the approach:
```rust use glob::Pattern;
pub struct ExcludeFilter {
    patterns: Vec<Pattern>,
}
impl ExcludeFilter {
    pub fn new(patterns: &[String]) -> Result<Self, glob::PatternError> {
        let compiled: Vec<Pattern> = patterns
            .iter()
            .map(|p| Pattern::new(p))
            .collect::<Result<Vec<_>, _>>()?;
        Ok(Self { patterns: compiled })
    }

    pub fn should_exclude(&self, path: &str) -> bool {
        self.patterns.iter().any(|p| p.matches(path))
    }
} ```
